Scenario 1: User changes current frame through UI controls
  Trigger examples:
    - User edits `ui->framePosition` spinbox (valueChanged)
    - User edits `ui->framePosition_2` spinbox (valueChanged)
    - User drags `ui->frameSlider` (valueChanged -> `frameSliderMoved`)
    - User clicks a CacheStatusWidget frame -> `seekFrame(frame)`

High-level connection(s) in `MainWindow::setupConnections()`:
  - `connect(ui->framePosition, QOverload<int>::of(&QSpinBox::valueChanged), this, &MainWindow::seekFrame);`
  - `connect(ui->framePosition_2, QOverload<int>::of(&QSpinBox::valueChanged), this, &MainWindow::seekFrame);`
  - `connect(ui->frameSlider, &QAbstractSlider::valueChanged, this, &MainWindow::frameSliderMoved);`
  - `connect(cacheStatusWidget, &CacheStatusWidget::frameClicked, this, [this](int frame) { seekFrame(frame); });`

Call trace (detailed):

1. UI spinbox change: `QSpinBox::valueChanged(int)` emitted
   -> Connected to
   2. `MainWindow::seekFrame(int frame)`

MainWindow::seekFrame:
  - Calls: `ui->videoLoader->seekToFrame(frame, false);`
    - note: `suppressEmit = false` here -> VideoLoader is expected to emit `frameChanged` when frame is displayed.
  - Then: `if (!ui->frameSlider->isSliderDown()) ui->frameSlider->setValue(frame);`
  - Returns to event loop.

VideoLoader::seekToFrame(int frameNumber, bool suppressEmit)
  - Bounds-check and qBound frameNumber against [0, totalFrames-1].
  - If `m_frameLoaderManager` exists:
      - `m_frameLoaderManager->resetPrioritiesForCurrentFrame(frameNumber, s_preloadRadius);`
      - `preloadAdjacentFrames(frameNumber, s_preloadRadius);`
  - Calls `displayFrame(frameNumber, suppressEmit);`

VideoLoader::displayFrame(int frameNumber, bool suppressEmit)
  - Quick checks: video open, frame range -> return early if invalid.
  - Optionally: again call `m_frameLoaderManager->resetPrioritiesForCurrentFrame(...)` (safety).
  - Tries to retrieve `CachedFrame* cached = m_frameCache->object(frameNumber);`
  - Branch here:

    Path A: Frame is in cache (synchronous, fast)
      - `if (cached && cached->original)` true:
        - `currentCvFrame = cached->original;`
        - If `cached->thresholded` present -> `m_thresholdedFrame_mono = *cached->thresholded;` else `m_thresholdedFrame_mono = cv::Mat()`
        - `frameFromCache = true;`
        - Set `currentFrameIdx = frameNumber`
        - Decide which QImage to produce:
            - If `m_activeViewModes` requests threshold and `m_thresholdedFrame_mono` available -> convert thresholded to `currentQImageFrame`
            - Else convert `*currentCvFrame` to `currentQImageFrame`
        - If `!suppressEmit`:
            - Emit `frameChanged(currentFrameIdx, currentQImageFrame);`
              * Emitted from UI thread (VideoLoader), with `frameNumber`.
        - `update()` (repaint)
      - End Path A.

    Path B: Frame is NOT in cache (async/disk or background)
      - Check current file position - attempt `videoCapture.set(CAP_PROP_POS_FRAMES, frameNumber)`
        - If `set()` fails:
            - Set `m_pendingSeekFrame = frameNumber`
            - If `m_frameLoaderManager`:
                - Build request: `FrameLoadRequest(frameNumber, priority=100, getCurrentThresholdSettings())`
                - `m_frameLoaderManager->requestFrames(reqs);`  // background will deliver via frameLoaded signal
            - Return (do NOT emit `frameChanged` now)
        - Else `set()` succeeded:
            - Attempt `videoCapture.read(*currentCvFrame)`:
              - If read success:
                  - Insert new `CachedFrame` into `m_frameCache` with original (threshold empty)
                  - Request background reprocessing for thresholded (`m_frameLoaderManager->requestFrames([...])`)
                  - Set `currentFrameIdx = frameNumber`
                  - Convert to `currentQImageFrame` (original)
                  - If `!suppressEmit`:
                      - Emit `frameChanged(currentFrameIdx, currentQImageFrame);`
                  - `update()`
              - If read fails:
                  - Clear `currentCvFrame` and `m_thresholdedFrame_mono`
                  - If `m_isPlaying` then `pause()` (playback halts)
                  - Return
      - End Path B.

VideoLoader asynchronous path (if frame was requested to background loader):
  - Background loader (FrameLoaderManager) will later emit:
      - `FrameLoaderManager::frameLoaded(int frameNumber, cv::Mat original, cv::Mat thresholded)`
        -> Connected to `VideoLoader::onFrameLoaded(int, cv::Mat, cv::Mat)`

VideoLoader::onFrameLoaded(int frameNumber, original, thresholded)
  - Insert/merge into `m_frameCache` (creates CachedFrame with original + optional thresholded).
  - Emit `frameCached(frameNumber);` (notify widgets like CacheStatusWidget / MiniLoaders).
  - Emit `frameEvicted(evictedFrames...)` for any evictions.
  - If `m_pendingSeekFrame == frameNumber`:
      - Clear `m_pendingSeekFrame = -1`
      - Choose which buffer to use (if threshold requested & available use thresholded)
      - Set `currentCvFrame` and `m_thresholdedFrame_mono`
      - `currentFrameIdx = frameNumber`
      - Convert to `currentQImageFrame` appropriately
      - Emit `frameChanged(currentFrameIdx, currentQImageFrame);`   <-- IMPORTANT: this will reach MainWindow (and others)
      - `update()` (repaint)

MainWindow connections listening to `VideoLoader::frameChanged`:
  - `connect(ui->videoLoader, &VideoLoader::frameChanged, this, &MainWindow::updateFrameDisplay, Qt::UniqueConnection);`
  - `connect(ui->videoLoader, &VideoLoader::frameChanged, this, &MainWindow::updateMiniLoaderCrop, Qt::UniqueConnection);`
  - Also `connect(ui->videoLoader, &VideoLoader::frameChanged, cacheStatusWidget, &CacheStatusWidget::onFrameCached)` was wired via a lambda earlier (cacheStatusWidget uses a lambda listening to `frameChanged` to set current).
  - Many other components react to `frameCached` and `frameChanged` (MiniLoaders, CacheStatusWidget, overlay widgets).

MainWindow::updateFrameDisplay(int currentFrameNumber, const QImage& currentFrame)
  - If `!ui->frameSlider->isSliderDown()` then `ui->frameSlider->setValue(currentFrameNumber);`
  - `ui->framePosition->setValue(currentFrameNumber);`
  - `ui->framePosition_2->setValue(currentFrameNumber);`
  - (Note: updateMiniLoaderCrop is also invoked via separate connection to update per-frame crops)

Other direct callers that lead to seek:
  - `MainWindow::frameSliderMoved(int value)`:
      - Calls: `ui->videoLoader->seekToFrame(value, false);`
      - If `!ui->framePosition->hasFocus()` set `ui->framePosition->setValue(value);`
  - `MainWindow::goToFirstFrame()` / `goToLastFrame()`:
      - Call `ui->videoLoader->seekToFrame(0/last, false)` and then update widgets.
  - `CacheStatusWidget::frameClicked` -> `MainWindow::seekFrame(frame)` -> follows above.

Summary of side-effects / listeners when `frameChanged` is emitted:
  - `MainWindow::updateFrameDisplay` (updates spinboxes & slider)
  - `MainWindow::updateMiniLoaderCrop` (calls into mini loaders to set expected frames)
  - `CacheStatusWidget::setCurrentFrame` (via the lambda joining to frameChanged)
  - `MiniLoader::onFrameCached` gets `frameCached` not `frameChanged`, but `onFrameLoaded` emits `frameCached` earlier
  - Any other slots connected to `VideoLoader::frameChanged` in UI will be invoked.

