Other noteworthy paths & interactions (cross-cutting):

- frameSlider -> user dragging slider:
  - `frameSliderMoved(int value)` called on `valueChanged`
  - `frameSliderMoved` calls `ui->videoLoader->seekToFrame(value, false);` and then updates `framePosition` spinbox if it does not have focus.
  - dragging slider also sets `ui->frameSlider->isSliderDown()` during drag; `updateFrameDisplay` won't update the slider value while slider is down (avoids feedback loops).

- Focus protection:
  - Many places update spinboxes only when they do not have focus to avoid changing what the user is currently editing:
    - Example: after seeking, MainWindow sets `ui->framePosition->setValue(currentFrameNumber);` but only FrameSlider is prevented from being overwritten if slider is down.
    - Seek callers also check `if (!ui->framePosition->hasFocus())` prior to writing to the spinbox.

- Mirrored widgets:
  - There are duplicate controls (`playPauseButton_2`, `framePosition_2`, `comboPlaybackSpeed_2`) that are mirrored. `setPlayButtonsState` handles mirroring of play buttons. Spinbox connections mirror both to `MainWindow::seekFrame`.

- `suppressEmit` behavior:
  - When `suppressEmit == true` passed to `displayFrame`, `displayFrame` will not call `emit frameChanged(...)`. However, if the frame must be loaded asynchronously (pending), `onFrameLoaded` will still emit `frameChanged` when the frame becomes available.
  - `play()` uses `seekToFrame(..., true)` to avoid an immediate `frameChanged` emission before starting the timer; the timer-driven `processNextFrame` will drive subsequent `displayFrame` emissions.

- Background/Cache interplay:
  - `m_frameCache` is checked frequently to decide synchronous vs asynchronous path.
  - Calls to `m_frameLoaderManager->requestFrames()` pass a copy of current threshold settings to ensure background precomputations match UI state.
  - `frameCached` is emitted when a cached insert completes; MiniLoaders and CacheStatusWidget listen to `frameCached`.
  - `onFrameLoaded` emits `frameEvicted` for any frames that got evicted due to QCache capacity.

- When user seeks to a frame that is out-of-range:
  - `seekToFrame` does `frameNumber = qBound(0, frameNumber, totalFramesCount > 0 ? totalFramesCount - 1 : 0);` so requests clamp to available range.

- If VideoLoader is not loaded (`!isVideoLoaded()`), `seekToFrame` and `play()` early-return; UI logic typically disables playback controls appropriately at load/unload.

