Concise sequence examples (two linear traces):

A) User ⇢ Spinbox valueChanged(123) ⇢ MainWindow::seekFrame(123)
   ⇢ VideoLoader::seekToFrame(123,false)
   ⇢ VideoLoader::preloadAdjacentFrames / resetPriorities
   ⇢ VideoLoader::displayFrame(123,false)
     - if cached -> set currentFrameIdx, currentQImageFrame, emit frameChanged(123,QImage)
     - else -> either (sync read -> same emit) OR (set m_pendingSeekFrame + requestFrames -> return)
       - if pending -> later FrameLoaderManager::frameLoaded -> VideoLoader::onFrameLoaded -> emit frameChanged(123,QImage)
   ⇢ MainWindow::updateFrameDisplay(123,QImage) -> spinboxes + slider updated
   ⇢ MainWindow::updateMiniLoaderCrop(123,QImage) -> mini loaders updated
   ⇢ CacheStatusWidget::onFrameCached (if cached) -> UI cache marker updated

B) User ⇢ Press `playPauseButton` (toggle true) ⇢ MainWindow::setPlayButtonsState(true)
   ⇢ ui->videoLoader->play()
   ⇢ VideoLoader::play() -> set m_isPlaying=true; playbackTimer->start()
   ⇢ playbackTimer timeout => VideoLoader::processNextFrame()
   ⇢ processNextFrame computes nextFrame = currentFrameIdx +1
     - if cache has nextFrame -> displayFrame(nextFrame) -> emit frameChanged(nextFrame) -> MainWindow update...
     - else -> m_pendingSeekFrame = nextFrame; request background load; return
   ⇢ Background onFrameLoaded(nextFrame, ...) -> VideoLoader::onFrameLoaded()
   ⇢ onFrameLoaded sees m_pendingSeekFrame==nextFrame -> sets currentFrameIdx and emits frameChanged(nextFrame)
   ⇢ MainWindow::updateFrameDisplay and other receivers invoked
   ⇢ Timer fires again -> processNextFrame continues to next frame

